body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting Car Dealership Support. My name is Justin Griffin. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Judy. How can I assist you today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I bought a car from your dealership, but I'm disappointed with it and would like to return it.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I'm sorry to hear that. To proceed with the return process, I'll need a bit more information from you. Could you provide me with the last four digits of your phone number, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's three zero zero eight.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for that information. One last thing, could you also provide me with the spelling of your current address?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Yes, it's P as in Papa, R as in Romeo, I as in India, M as in Mike, and E as in Echo.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Judy, for sharing that. I will initiate the return process with the details provided. Your feedback is important to us. Thank you for your time and patience.

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Thank you, Justin, for your help. I appreciate it.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: You're welcome, Judy. If you have any further questions, feel free to reach out. Have a great day!
